ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend this course - all of this information and practice seems very important before actually doing assessments and eventually treatment with patients.
I would recommend this class to a fellow student as all the material was highly relevant to our current clinical training and clinical research.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Great introduction to diagnostic assessment; I'm looking forward to next semester!

This course contributed greatly to my understanding of clinical assessment and practice, and it also gave me some things to think about regarding research questions. The instructor was knowledgeable both about clinical practice and about relevant research.
This course contributed to my research as it improved my understanding of how we currently conceptualize our diagnostic system and the flaws of our current system.
